# ğŸ—ï¸ mkarchi

mkarchi (make architecture) is a command-line tool that generates complete project structures from simple tree-format text files.  
Define your entire project architecture â€” folders, files, and even file contents â€” in one readable text file, then generate it instantly with a single command.

---

# âœ¨ Features

- ğŸ“ Create directories from a tree structure  
- ğŸ“„ Create empty files automatically  
- âœï¸ Create files with content using intuitive `{ }` syntax  
- ğŸ¯ Preserve indentation (perfect for Python, YAML, JSON, etc.)  
- ğŸ’¬ Support comments in structure files  
- ğŸš€ Fast & simple â€” build your whole project in one command  

---

# ğŸ“¦ Installation

#### âœ… Recommended (via pip)

```bash
pip install mkarchi
```
Option 2: Install from source
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/mkarchi.git
cd mkarchi
pip install -e .
```
Option 3: Run as module (no installation)
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/mkarchi.git
cd mkarchi
python -m mkarchi apply structure.txt
```
