# ğŸ“„ Structure File Format
### ğŸ“ Create Directories
Directories must end with /:

```text
Copy code
my_folder/
â”œâ”€â”€ subfolder/
â””â”€â”€ another_folder/
```
### ğŸ“„ Create Empty Files
Files without { } are created empty:

```text
my_folder/
â”œâ”€â”€ empty_file.txt
â””â”€â”€ config.json
```
### âœï¸ Create Files with Content
Use { } to define file content:

```text
script.py{
    print("Hello!")
    print("This is Python code")
}
```
### ğŸ¯ Indentation Preservation
mkarchi automatically preserves indentation:

```text

utils.py{
    def greet(name):
        if name:
            print(f"Hello, {name}!")
        else:
            print("Hello, World!")
}
```
Result (utils.py):

```python
def greet(name):
    if name:
        print(f"Hello, {name}!")
    else:
        print("Hello, World!")
```
### ğŸ’¬ Comments Support
Use # for comments in your structure file:

```text
project/
â”œâ”€â”€ src/          # Source code
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ main.py   # Entry point
â””â”€â”€ tests/        # Tests
```
